Yes, I was familiar with LAUGH LINES. It's been 40 years since I started to learn English so I probably know it better than you'd think. It's slang that often stumps me, especially of the regional variety.

The rags one might wear are called "łachmany" in Polish, so our "szmata" is possibly not as versatile as your rags. However, a tabloid is salngiky called "szmatławiec", which is a direct counterpart of your rags for a newspaper.

